Example Ddown Document
=====================

Introduction
------------

This is a simple example of a Ddown document. It demonstrates the basic features of the Ddown syntax.

Lists in Ddown {@color: #8E44AD; background-color: #3498DB;}
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~

=> Unordered list items use the "=>" prefix
=> They can span multiple lines
=> And can have inline styles {@font-weight: bold;}

1. Ordered lists use numbers
2. Just like in regular markdown
3. They're quite straightforward

Code Example
------------

```python
def hello_ddown():
    print("Hello from Ddown!")
    return True

# This is a Python code block
hello_ddown()
```

Styling and Links
---------------

=> You can add [links to websites](https://example.com)
=> And include images: ![Ddown Logo](https://example.com/ddown.png)
=> Blockquotes work too:

> This is a blockquote in Ddown.
> It can span multiple lines.

